message: The vial tool is crucial! It works best on 'solid' ingredients, creating extracts. Using it on a 'solid, mundane' ingredient yields a mundane extract (value 30), and on a 'solid, magical' ingredient yields a magical extract (value 30). The highest value item (100) is consistently achieved by combining ONE 'liquid, extracted, mundane' item with ONE 'liquid, extracted, magical' item. Avoid using the vial on 'liquid' or 'gas' ingredients, as it often results in botched extractions (negative value). The filter tool seemed to worsen already botched items, so its optimal use is unclear or for a different purpose.

message: The ğŸ§ª vial tool is best used on *solid* ingredients to create valuable extracts (e.g., solid -> 30 value). Avoid using the vial on liquid or gas ingredients, as this results in negative value 'botched extractions'. The ğŸ§« filter tool consistently decreased the value of items in my playthroughs; avoid using it. For combinations, aim for a 'solid extract' (mundane) with a 'magical liquid' (raw ingredient or another magical extract) for high values (70-80). Combining two mundane 'solid extracts' is also good (60 value). Combining three or more items almost always leads to 'overcomplicated' items with negative value. Combining two raw liquid ingredients (magical + mundane) gives moderate value (40), but raw gas combinations resulted in negative values. Focus on creating solid extracts and combining them strategically with magical liquids.
